reviewText: I have never owned a dvd of Tracey's until this one and it's a challenge! I enjoy Jillian Michaels, Cindy Whitmarsh and Jackie Warner and this one was up there- probably harder! The three sections offer variety depending on the amount of time a person has. The total body was a challenge! It says it's 25 minutes but with the warm-up it came in about 35 min. This is a great dvd for someone looking for a challenge!

reviewText: I purchased this after reading the reviews on Amazon about the video, good and bad. I'm glad I did not listen to the bad reviews and not purchase. The core workout is 14 minutes, the lower body is 31 minutes and the total body is 33 minutes. When I combine the total body and core workout I burn almost 300 calories in under 40 minutes. Yes, she does engage your lower back, but just modify it. I had back surgery in 1997, so I'm picky about workouts as sometimes certain types will aggravate my back. So with Tracey's workout, I simply modify and still get an effective workout and a great calorie burn. For example, instead of doing plank holds with leg raises on my feet, I do them on my knees so I don't strain my back. If you're looking for a shorter, effecive workout that will leave you sore the next day then this is a must buy! I use this during the week when I have to work and can't do a complete 60 to 80 minute workout. FYI, I just ordered her other two workouts (New Body and Barre Arms/Abs) because I love this one so much!

reviewText: I'm an intermediate to advanced exerciser and usually love cross-training, HIIT, and compound exercises. However, this DVD was super disappointing. Although it WILL work you, the moves are a lot more convoluted than they need to be to get a good workout, which is not ideal for someone like me who is nursing old lower back and knee injuries. And it's hard to take Tracey Mallett seriously when she says "hexhale" over and over again or when she talks about "lactating" to refer to lactic acid buildup. No, thank you.

reviewText: I have never bought a Tracey Mallet workout before, this was my first one. I saw ads for this and it looked fast paced but not so fast you might fall over afterwards. I was really wrong. This workout is challenging. My legs and arms were sore for days. It was actually fun. Tracey is upbeat and happy, but not get on your nerves happy. I like that she actaully does this the whole workout with you. I am looking forward to when I can actaully finish the whole dvd.

reviewText: I have a great number of exercise dvds but stick to those I know like Jari Love, Jillian Michaels, Bob  Harper, Amy Dixon and Kelly Coffey-Meyer. I was not sure about trying this as I was not sure it would be intense enough. However, I love it. The cardio segements are good. I up the intensity of some of them. The leg segment is wonderful and you still get a decent arm workout with the static holding of the light weights. I am finding that I do this workout nearly every week since I got it so it is fitting well into my rotation.
summary: First time I have tried Tracey Mallet and really like it

reviewText: I received this workout on Monday,watched it before I did it.I did the whole thing the first time yesterday the day after I received it.If you choose to do the whole workout it runs about 1 hour and 15 minutes.You can also choose to do the workouts seperate.I really enjoyed it.I admit there were some of the moves that I hadn't done before,it will take some getting use to on SOME of the moves,but I really enjoyed it.After the warm up Tracey starts on weight work.By the time we were done with the first weight work I was breathing hard and sweating.I liked the cardio parts,they are Tabata style and I liked that.By the time I got done with the whole workout I was huffing and puffing and sweating bullets.I did have to pause a couple of times to catch my breath.Today the day after the workout I'am sore,in my booty, both sides of my waists,and shoulders.In my opinion IF your not at least huffing and puffing and sweating bullets by the end of the whole workout, you didn't do it right.This will be in my rotation.This is the first Tracey Mallett workout that I have ordered,and I like her.She is sweet,calm talking,NOT hollering at you,she has a calm voice.Will consider ordering more of her workouts.After I got done I felt energized.So glad I bought it.Oh,and the music I absolutely love it,it's got a good beat to it,Very motivating,or I think it is anyway.
summary: I love this workout by Tracey!!
